#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:14(para) 
msgid "This release contains a variety of fixes from 9.0.3. For information about new features in the 9.0 major release, see <xref linkend=\"release-9-0\"/>."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:21(title) 
msgid "Migration to Version 9.0.4"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:23(para) /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:367(para) /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:543(para) /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:990(para) 
msgid "A dump/restore is not required for those running 9.0.X."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:27(para) 
msgid "However, if your installation was upgraded from a previous major release by running <application>pg_upgrade</application>, you should take action to prevent possible data loss due to a now-fixed bug in <application>pg_upgrade</application>. The recommended solution is to run <command>VACUUM FREEZE</command> on all TOAST tables. More information is available at <ulink url=\"http://wiki.postgresql.org/wiki/20110408pg_upgrade_fix\"> http://wiki.postgresql.org/wiki/20110408pg_upgrade_fix</ulink>."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:41(title) /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:374(title) /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:550(title) /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:997(title) /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1624(title) 
msgid "Changes"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:46(para) 
msgid "Fix <application>pg_upgrade</application>'s handling of TOAST tables (Bruce Momjian)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:51(para) 
msgid "The <structname>pg_class</structname>.<structfield>relfrozenxid</structfield> value for TOAST tables was not correctly copied into the new installation during <application>pg_upgrade</application>. This could later result in <literal>pg_clog</literal> files being discarded while they were still needed to validate tuples in the TOAST tables, leading to <quote>could not access status of transaction</quote> failures."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:60(para) 
msgid "This error poses a significant risk of data loss for installations that have been upgraded with <application>pg_upgrade</application>. This patch corrects the problem for future uses of <application>pg_upgrade</application>, but does not in itself cure the issue in installations that have been processed with a buggy version of <application>pg_upgrade</application>."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:70(para) 
msgid "Suppress incorrect <quote>PD_ALL_VISIBLE flag was incorrectly set</quote> warning (Heikki Linnakangas)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:75(para) 
msgid "<command>VACUUM</command> would sometimes issue this warning in cases that are actually valid."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:82(para) 
msgid "Use better SQLSTATE error codes for hot standby conflict cases (Tatsuo Ishii and Simon Riggs)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:87(para) 
msgid "All retryable conflict errors now have an error code that indicates that a retry is possible. Also, session closure due to the database being dropped on the master is now reported as <literal>ERRCODE_DATABASE_DROPPED</literal>, rather than <literal>ERRCODE_ADMIN_SHUTDOWN</literal>, so that connection poolers can handle the situation correctly."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:98(para) 
msgid "Prevent intermittent hang in interactions of startup process with bgwriter process (Simon Riggs)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:103(para) 
msgid "This affected recovery in non-hot-standby cases."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:109(para) 
msgid "Disallow including a composite type in itself (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:113(para) 
msgid "This prevents scenarios wherein the server could recurse infinitely while processing the composite type. While there are some possible uses for such a structure, they don't seem compelling enough to justify the effort required to make sure it always works safely."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:122(para) 
msgid "Avoid potential deadlock during catalog cache initialization (Nikhil Sontakke)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:127(para) 
msgid "In some cases the cache loading code would acquire share lock on a system index before locking the index's catalog. This could deadlock against processes trying to acquire exclusive locks in the other, more standard order."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:136(para) 
msgid "Fix dangling-pointer problem in <literal>BEFORE ROW UPDATE</literal> trigger handling when there was a concurrent update to the target tuple (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:142(para) 
msgid "This bug has been observed to result in intermittent <quote>cannot extract system attribute from virtual tuple</quote> failures while trying to do <literal>UPDATE RETURNING ctid</literal>. There is a very small probability of more serious errors, such as generating incorrect index entries for the updated tuple."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:152(para) 
msgid "Disallow <command>DROP TABLE</command> when there are pending deferred trigger events for the table (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:157(para) 
msgid "Formerly the <command>DROP</command> would go through, leading to <quote>could not open relation with OID nnn</quote> errors when the triggers were eventually fired."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:165(para) 
msgid "Allow <quote>replication</quote> as a user name in <filename>pg_hba.conf</filename> (Andrew Dunstan)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:170(para) 
msgid "<quote>replication</quote> is special in the database name column, but it was mistakenly also treated as special in the user name column."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:177(para) 
msgid "Prevent crash triggered by constant-false WHERE conditions during GEQO optimization (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:187(para) 
msgid "Improve planner's handling of semi-join and anti-join cases (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:194(para) 
msgid "Fix handling of <literal>SELECT FOR UPDATE</literal> in a sub-SELECT (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:199(para) 
msgid "This bug typically led to <quote>cannot extract system attribute from virtual tuple</quote> errors."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:206(para) 
msgid "Fix selectivity estimation for text search to account for NULLs (Jesper Krogh)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:213(para) 
msgid "Fix get_actual_variable_range() to support hypothetical indexes injected by an index adviser plugin (Gurjeet Singh)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:220(para) 
msgid "Fix PL/Python memory leak involving array slices (Daniel Popowich)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:226(para) 
msgid "Allow <application>libpq</application>'s SSL initialization to succeed when user's home directory is unavailable (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:231(para) 
msgid "If the SSL mode is such that a root certificate file is not required, there is no need to fail. This change restores the behavior to what it was in pre-9.0 releases."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:239(para) 
msgid "Fix <application>libpq</application> to return a useful error message for errors detected in <function>conninfo_array_parse</function> (Joseph Adams)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:244(para) 
msgid "A typo caused the library to return NULL, rather than the <structname>PGconn</structname> structure containing the error message, to the application."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:252(para) 
msgid "Fix <application>ecpg</application> preprocessor's handling of float constants (Heikki Linnakangas)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:259(para) 
msgid "Fix parallel <application>pg_restore</application> to handle comments on POST_DATA items correctly (Arnd Hannemann)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:266(para) 
msgid "Fix <application>pg_restore</application> to cope with long lines (over 1KB) in TOC files (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:273(para) 
msgid "Put in more safeguards against crashing due to division-by-zero with overly enthusiastic compiler optimization (Aurelien Jarno)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:280(para) 
msgid "Support use of dlopen() in FreeBSD and OpenBSD on MIPS (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:284(para) 
msgid "There was a hard-wired assumption that this system function was not available on MIPS hardware on these systems. Use a compile-time test instead, since more recent versions have it."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:292(para) 
msgid "Fix compilation failures on HP-UX (Heikki Linnakangas)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:298(para) 
msgid "Avoid crash when trying to write to the Windows console very early in process startup (Rushabh Lathia)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:305(para) 
msgid "Support building with MinGW 64 bit compiler for Windows (Andrew Dunstan)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:312(para) 
msgid "Fix version-incompatibility problem with <application>libintl</application> on Windows (Hiroshi Inoue)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:319(para) 
msgid "Fix usage of <application>xcopy</application> in Windows build scripts to work correctly under Windows 7 (Andrew Dunstan)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:324(para) 
msgid "This affects the build scripts only, not installation or usage."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:330(para) 
msgid "Fix path separator used by <application>pg_regress</application> on Cygwin (Andrew Dunstan)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:337(para) 
msgid "Update time zone data files to <application>tzdata</application> release 2011f for DST law changes in Chile, Cuba, Falkland Islands, Morocco, Samoa, and Turkey; also historical corrections for South Australia, Alaska, and Hawaii."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:351(title) 
msgid "Release 9.0.3"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:355(simpara) 
msgid "2011-01-31"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:358(para) 
msgid "This release contains a variety of fixes from 9.0.2. For information about new features in the 9.0 major release, see <xref linkend=\"release-9-0\"/>."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:365(title) 
msgid "Migration to Version 9.0.3"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:379(para) 
msgid "Before exiting <application>walreceiver</application>, ensure all the received WAL is fsync'd to disk (Heikki Linnakangas)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:384(para) 
msgid "Otherwise the standby server could replay some un-synced WAL, conceivably leading to data corruption if the system crashes just at that point."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:391(para) 
msgid "Avoid excess fsync activity in <application>walreceiver</application> (Heikki Linnakangas)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:398(para) 
msgid "Make <command>ALTER TABLE</command> revalidate uniqueness and exclusion constraints when needed (Noah Misch)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:403(para) 
msgid "This was broken in 9.0 by a change that was intended to suppress revalidation during <command>VACUUM FULL</command> and <command>CLUSTER</command>, but unintentionally affected <command>ALTER TABLE</command> as well."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:411(para) 
msgid "Fix EvalPlanQual for <command>UPDATE</command> of an inheritance tree in which the tables are not all alike (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:416(para) 
msgid "Any variation in the table row types (including dropped columns present in only some child tables) would confuse the EvalPlanQual code, leading to misbehavior or even crashes. Since EvalPlanQual is only executed during concurrent updates to the same row, the problem was only seen intermittently."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:426(para) 
msgid "Avoid failures when <command>EXPLAIN</command> tries to display a simple-form <literal>CASE</literal> expression (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:431(para) 
msgid "If the <literal>CASE</literal>'s test expression was a constant, the planner could simplify the <literal>CASE</literal> into a form that confused the expression-display code, resulting in <quote>unexpected CASE WHEN clause</quote> errors."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:440(para) 
msgid "Fix assignment to an array slice that is before the existing range of subscripts (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:445(para) 
msgid "If there was a gap between the newly added subscripts and the first pre-existing subscript, the code miscalculated how many entries needed to be copied from the old array's null bitmap, potentially leading to data corruption or crash."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:454(para) 
msgid "Avoid unexpected conversion overflow in planner for very distant date values (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:459(para) 
msgid "The <type>date</type> type supports a wider range of dates than can be represented by the <type>timestamp</type> types, but the planner assumed it could always convert a date to timestamp with impunity."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:467(para) 
msgid "Fix PL/Python crash when an array contains null entries (Alex Hunsaker)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:473(para) 
msgid "Remove <application>ecpg</application>'s fixed length limit for constants defining an array dimension (Michael Meskes)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:480(para) 
msgid "Fix erroneous parsing of <type>tsquery</type> values containing <literal>... &amp; !(subexpression) | ...</literal> (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:485(para) 
msgid "Queries containing this combination of operators were not executed correctly. The same error existed in <filename>contrib/intarray</filename>'s <type>query_int</type> type and <filename>contrib/ltree</filename>'s <type>ltxtquery</type> type."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:494(para) 
msgid "Fix buffer overrun in <filename>contrib/intarray</filename>'s input function for the <type>query_int</type> type (Apple)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:499(para) 
msgid "This bug is a security risk since the function's return address could be overwritten. Thanks to Apple Inc's security team for reporting this issue and supplying the fix. (CVE-2010-4015)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:507(para) 
msgid "Fix bug in <filename>contrib/seg</filename>'s GiST picksplit algorithm (Alexander Korotkov)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:512(para) 
msgid "This could result in considerable inefficiency, though not actually incorrect answers, in a GiST index on a <type>seg</type> column. If you have such an index, consider <command>REINDEX</command>ing it after installing this update. (This is identical to the bug that was fixed in <filename>contrib/cube</filename> in the previous update.)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:527(title) 
msgid "Release 9.0.2"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:531(simpara) 
msgid "2010-12-16"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:534(para) 
msgid "This release contains a variety of fixes from 9.0.1. For information about new features in the 9.0 major release, see <xref linkend=\"release-9-0\"/>."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:541(title) 
msgid "Migration to Version 9.0.2"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:555(para) 
msgid "Force the default <link linkend=\"guc-wal-sync-method\"><varname>wal_sync_method</varname></link> to be <literal>fdatasync</literal> on Linux (Tom Lane, Marti Raudsepp)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:561(para) 
msgid "The default on Linux has actually been <literal>fdatasync</literal> for many years, but recent kernel changes caused <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> to choose <literal>open_datasync</literal> instead. This choice did not result in any performance improvement, and caused outright failures on certain filesystems, notably <literal>ext4</literal> with the <literal>data=journal</literal> mount option."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:572(para) 
msgid "Fix <quote>too many KnownAssignedXids</quote> error during Hot Standby replay (Heikki Linnakangas)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:579(para) 
msgid "Fix race condition in lock acquisition during Hot Standby (Simon Riggs)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:585(para) 
msgid "Avoid unnecessary conflicts during Hot Standby (Simon Riggs)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:589(para) 
msgid "This fixes some cases where replay was considered to conflict with standby queries (causing delay of replay or possibly cancellation of the queries), but there was no real conflict."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:597(para) 
msgid "Fix assorted bugs in WAL replay logic for GIN indexes (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:601(para) 
msgid "This could result in <quote>bad buffer id: 0</quote> failures or corruption of index contents during replication."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:608(para) 
msgid "Fix recovery from base backup when the starting checkpoint WAL record is not in the same WAL segment as its redo point (Jeff Davis)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:615(para) 
msgid "Fix corner-case bug when streaming replication is enabled immediately after creating the master database cluster (Heikki Linnakangas)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:622(para) 
msgid "Fix persistent slowdown of autovacuum workers when multiple workers remain active for a long time (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:627(para) 
msgid "The effective <varname>vacuum_cost_limit</varname> for an autovacuum worker could drop to nearly zero if it processed enough tables, causing it to run extremely slowly."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:635(para) 
msgid "Fix long-term memory leak in autovacuum launcher (Alvaro Herrera)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:641(para) 
msgid "Avoid failure when trying to report an impending transaction wraparound condition from outside a transaction (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:646(para) 
msgid "This oversight prevented recovery after transaction wraparound got too close, because database startup processing would fail."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:653(para) 
msgid "Add support for detecting register-stack overrun on <literal>IA64</literal> (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:658(para) 
msgid "The <literal>IA64</literal> architecture has two hardware stacks. Full prevention of stack-overrun failures requires checking both."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:665(para) 
msgid "Add a check for stack overflow in <function>copyObject()</function> (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:669(para) 
msgid "Certain code paths could crash due to stack overflow given a sufficiently complex query."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:676(para) 
msgid "Fix detection of page splits in temporary GiST indexes (Heikki Linnakangas)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:681(para) 
msgid "It is possible to have a <quote>concurrent</quote> page split in a temporary index, if for example there is an open cursor scanning the index when an insertion is done. GiST failed to detect this case and hence could deliver wrong results when execution of the cursor continued."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:691(para) 
msgid "Fix error checking during early connection processing (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:695(para) 
msgid "The check for too many child processes was skipped in some cases, possibly leading to postmaster crash when attempting to add the new child process to fixed-size arrays."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:703(para) 
msgid "Improve efficiency of window functions (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:707(para) 
msgid "Certain cases where a large number of tuples needed to be read in advance, but <varname>work_mem</varname> was large enough to allow them all to be held in memory, were unexpectedly slow. <function>percent_rank()</function>, <function>cume_dist()</function> and <function>ntile()</function> in particular were subject to this problem."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:717(para) 
msgid "Avoid memory leakage while <command>ANALYZE</command>'ing complex index expressions (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:724(para) 
msgid "Ensure an index that uses a whole-row Var still depends on its table (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:729(para) 
msgid "An index declared like <literal>create index i on t (foo(t.*))</literal> would not automatically get dropped when its table was dropped."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:736(para) 
msgid "Add missing support in <command>DROP OWNED BY</command> for removing foreign data wrapper/server privileges belonging to a user (Heikki Linnakangas)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:743(para) 
msgid "Do not <quote>inline</quote> a SQL function with multiple <literal>OUT</literal> parameters (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:748(para) 
msgid "This avoids a possible crash due to loss of information about the expected result rowtype."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:755(para) 
msgid "Fix crash when inline-ing a set-returning function whose argument list contains a reference to an inline-able user function (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:762(para) 
msgid "Behave correctly if <literal>ORDER BY</literal>, <literal>LIMIT</literal>, <literal>FOR UPDATE</literal>, or <literal>WITH</literal> is attached to the <literal>VALUES</literal> part of <literal>INSERT ... VALUES</literal> (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:770(para) 
msgid "Make the <literal>OFF</literal> keyword unreserved (Heikki Linnakangas)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:774(para) 
msgid "This prevents problems with using <literal>off</literal> as a variable name in <application>PL/pgSQL</application>. That worked before 9.0, but was now broken because <application>PL/pgSQL</application> now treats all core reserved words as reserved."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:783(para) 
msgid "Fix constant-folding of <literal>COALESCE()</literal> expressions (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:787(para) 
msgid "The planner would sometimes attempt to evaluate sub-expressions that in fact could never be reached, possibly leading to unexpected errors."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:794(para) 
msgid "Fix <quote>could not find pathkey item to sort</quote> planner failure with comparison of whole-row Vars (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:801(para) 
