msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1637(para) 
msgid "PostgreSQL's existing standby-server capability has been expanded both to support read-only queries on standby servers and to greatly reduce the lag between master and standby servers. For many users, this will be a useful and low-administration form of replication, either for high availability or for horizontal scalability."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1647(para) 
msgid "Allow a standby server to accept read-only queries (Simon Riggs, Heikki Linnakangas)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1652(para) 
msgid "This feature is called Hot Standby. There are new <filename>postgresql.conf</filename> and <filename>recovery.conf</filename> settings to control this feature, as well as extensive <link linkend=\"hot-standby\">documentation</link>."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1661(para) 
msgid "Allow write-ahead log (<acronym>WAL</acronym>) data to be streamed to a standby server (Fujii Masao, Heikki Linnakangas)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1666(para) 
msgid "This feature is called Streaming Replication. Previously <acronym>WAL</acronym> data could be sent to standby servers only in units of entire <acronym>WAL</acronym> files (normally 16 megabytes each). Streaming Replication eliminates this inefficiency and allows updates on the master to be propagated to standby servers with very little delay. There are new <filename>postgresql.conf</filename> and <filename>recovery.conf</filename> settings to control this feature, as well as extensive <link linkend=\"streaming-replication\">documentation</link>."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1679(para) 
msgid "Add <link linkend=\"functions-recovery-info-table\"><function>pg_last_xlog_receive_location()</function></link> and <function>pg_last_xlog_replay_location()</function>, which can be used to monitor standby server <acronym>WAL</acronym> activity (Simon Riggs, Fujii Masao, Heikki Linnakangas)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1693(title) 
msgid "Performance"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1698(para) 
msgid "Allow per-tablespace values to be set for sequential and random page cost estimates (<varname>seq_page_cost</varname>/<varname>random_page_cost</varname>) via <link linkend=\"sql-altertablespace\"><command>ALTER TABLESPACE ... SET/RESET</command></link> (Robert Haas)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1707(para) 
msgid "Improve performance and reliability of EvalPlanQual rechecks in join queries (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1712(para) 
msgid "<command>UPDATE</command>, <command>DELETE</command>, and <command>SELECT FOR UPDATE/SHARE</command> queries that involve joins will now behave much better when encountering freshly-updated rows."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1720(para) 
msgid "Improve performance of <link linkend=\"sql-truncate\"><command>TRUNCATE</command></link> when the table was created or truncated earlier in the same transaction (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1729(para) 
msgid "Improve performance of finding inheritance child tables (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1739(title) 
msgid "Optimizer"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1744(para) 
msgid "Remove unnecessary <link linkend=\"queries-join\">outer joins</link> (Robert Haas)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1749(para) 
msgid "Outer joins where the inner side is unique and not referenced above the join are unnecessary and are therefore now removed. This will accelerate many automatically generated queries, such as those created by object-relational mappers (ORMs)."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1758(para) 
msgid "Allow <literal>IS NOT NULL</literal> restrictions to use indexes (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1762(para) 
msgid "This is particularly useful for finding <function>MAX()</function>/<function>MIN()</function> values in indexes that contain many null values."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1770(para) 
msgid "Improve the optimizer's choices about when to use materialize nodes, and when to use sorting versus hashing for <literal>DISTINCT</literal> (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1778(para) 
msgid "Improve the optimizer's equivalence detection for expressions involving <type>boolean</type><literal>&lt;&gt;</literal> operators (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1787(link) 
msgid "GEQO"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1792(para) 
msgid "Use the same random seed every time GEQO plans a query (Andres Freund)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1797(para) 
msgid "While the Genetic Query Optimizer (GEQO) still selects random plans, it now always selects the same random plans for identical queries, thus giving more consistent performance. You can modify <link linkend=\"guc-geqo-seed\"><varname>geqo_seed</varname></link> to experiment with alternative plans."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1807(para) 
msgid "Improve GEQO plan selection (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1811(para) 
msgid "This avoids the rare error <quote>failed to make a valid plan</quote>, and should also improve planning speed."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1822(title) 
msgid "Optimizer Statistics"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1827(para) 
msgid "Improve <link linkend=\"sql-analyze\"><command>ANALYZE</command></link> to support inheritance-tree statistics (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1832(para) 
msgid "This is particularly useful for partitioned tables. However, autovacuum does not yet automatically re-analyze parent tables when child tables change."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1840(para) 
msgid "Improve <link linkend=\"routine-vacuuming\">autovacuum</link>'s detection of when re-analyze is necessary (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1847(para) 
msgid "Improve optimizer's estimation for greater/less-than comparisons (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1852(para) 
msgid "When looking up statistics for greater/less-than comparisons, if the comparison value is in the first or last histogram bucket, use an index (if available) to fetch the current actual column minimum or maximum. This greatly improves the accuracy of estimates for comparison values near the ends of the data range, particularly if the range is constantly changing due to addition of new data."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1863(para) 
msgid "Allow setting of number-of-distinct-values statistics using <link linkend=\"sql-altertable\"><command>ALTER TABLE</command></link> (Robert Haas)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1869(para) 
msgid "This allows users to override the estimated number or percentage of distinct values for a column. This statistic is normally computed by <command>ANALYZE</command>, but the estimate can be poor, especially on tables with very large numbers of rows."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1882(title) 
msgid "Authentication"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1887(para) 
msgid "Add support for <link linkend=\"auth-radius\"><acronym>RADIUS</acronym></link> (Remote Authentication Dial In User Service) authentication (Magnus Hagander)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1896(para) 
msgid "Allow <link linkend=\"auth-ldap\"><acronym>LDAP</acronym></link> (Lightweight Directory Access Protocol) authentication to operate in <quote>search/bind</quote> mode (Robert Fleming, Magnus Hagander)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1903(para) 
msgid "This allows the user to be looked up first, then the system uses the <acronym>DN</acronym> (Distinguished Name) returned for that user."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1910(para) 
msgid "Add <link linkend=\"auth-pg-hba-conf\"><literal>samehost</literal></link> and <literal>samenet</literal> designations to <filename>pg_hba.conf</filename> (Stef Walter)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1917(para) 
msgid "These match the server's <acronym>IP</acronym> address and subnet address respectively."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1924(para) 
msgid "Pass trusted SSL root certificate names to the client so the client can return an appropriate client certificate (Craig Ringer)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1935(title) 
msgid "Monitoring"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1940(para) 
msgid "Add the ability for clients to set an <link linkend=\"libpq-connect-application-name\">application name</link>, which is displayed in <structname>pg_stat_activity</structname> (Dave Page)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1947(para) 
msgid "This allows administrators to characterize database traffic and troubleshoot problems by source application."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1954(para) 
msgid "Add a SQLSTATE option (<literal>%e</literal>) to <link linkend=\"guc-log-line-prefix\"><varname>log_line_prefix</varname></link> (Guillaume Smet)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1960(para) 
msgid "This allows users to compile statistics on errors and messages by error code number."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1968(para) 
msgid "Write to the Windows event log in <acronym>UTF16</acronym> encoding (Itagaki Takahiro)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1973(para) 
msgid "Now there is true multilingual support for PostgreSQL log messages on Windows."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1984(title) 
msgid "Statistics Counters"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1989(para) 
msgid "Add <link linkend=\"monitoring-stats-funcs-table\"><function>pg_stat_reset_shared('bgwriter')</function></link> to reset the cluster-wide shared statistics for the background writer (Greg Smith)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:1998(para) 
msgid "Add <link linkend=\"monitoring-stats-funcs-table\"><function>pg_stat_reset_single_table_counters()</function></link> and <function>pg_stat_reset_single_function_counters()</function> to allow resetting the statistics counters for individual tables and functions (Magnus Hagander)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2017(para) 
msgid "Allow setting of configuration parameters based on <link linkend=\"sql-alterrole\">database/role combinations</link> (Alvaro Herrera)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2023(para) 
msgid "Previously only per-database and per-role settings were possible, not combinations. All role and database settings are now stored in the new <structname>pg_db_role_setting</structname> system catalog. A new <application>psql</application> command <literal>\\drds</literal> shows these settings. The legacy system views <structname>pg_roles</structname>, <structname>pg_shadow</structname>, and <structname>pg_user</structname> do not show combination settings, and therefore no longer completely represent the configuration for a user or database."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2036(para) 
msgid "Add server parameter <link linkend=\"guc-bonjour\"><varname>bonjour</varname></link>, which controls whether a Bonjour-enabled server advertises itself via <productname>Bonjour</productname> (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2043(para) 
msgid "The default is off, meaning it does not advertise. This allows packagers to distribute Bonjour-enabled builds without worrying that individual users might not want the feature."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2051(para) 
msgid "Add server parameter <link linkend=\"guc-enable-material\"><varname>enable_material</varname></link>, which controls the use of materialize nodes in the optimizer (Robert Haas)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2058(para) 
msgid "The default is on. When off, the optimizer will not add materialize nodes purely for performance reasons, though they will still be used when necessary for correctness."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2066(para) 
msgid "Change server parameter <link linkend=\"guc-log-temp-files\"><varname>log_temp_files</varname></link> to use default file size units of kilobytes (Robert Haas)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2072(para) 
msgid "Previously this setting was interpreted in bytes if no units were specified."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2079(para) 
msgid "Log changes of parameter values when <filename>postgresql.conf</filename> is reloaded (Peter Eisentraut)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2084(para) 
msgid "This lets administrators and security staff audit changes of database settings, and is also very convenient for checking the effects of <filename>postgresql.conf</filename> edits."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2092(para) 
msgid "Properly enforce superuser permissions for custom server parameters (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2097(para) 
msgid "Non-superusers can no longer issue <command>ALTER ROLE</command>/<command>DATABASE SET</command> for parameters that are not currently known to the server. This allows the server to correctly check that superuser-only parameters are only set by superusers. Previously, the <literal>SET</literal> would be allowed and then ignored at session start, making superuser-only custom parameters much less useful than they should be."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2120(para) 
msgid "Perform <link linkend=\"sql-for-update-share\"><command>SELECT FOR UPDATE</command>/<literal>SHARE</literal></link> processing after applying <literal>LIMIT</literal>, so the number of rows returned is always predictable (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2127(para) 
msgid "Previously, changes made by concurrent transactions could cause a <command>SELECT FOR UPDATE</command> to unexpectedly return fewer rows than specified by its <literal>LIMIT</literal>. <literal>FOR UPDATE</literal> in combination with <literal>ORDER BY</literal> can still produce surprising results, but that can be corrected by placing <literal>FOR UPDATE</literal> in a subquery."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2137(para) 
msgid "Allow mixing of traditional and SQL-standard <link linkend=\"sql-limit\"><literal>LIMIT</literal>/<literal>OFFSET</literal></link> syntax (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2145(para) 
msgid "Extend the supported frame options in <link linkend=\"sql-window\">window functions</link> (Hitoshi Harada)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2151(para) 
msgid "Frames can now start with <literal>CURRENT ROW</literal>, and the <literal>ROWS <replaceable>n</replaceable> PRECEDING</literal>/<literal>FOLLOWING</literal> options are now supported."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2159(para) 
msgid "Make <command>SELECT INTO</command> and <command>CREATE TABLE AS</command> return row counts to the client in their command tags (Boszormenyi Zoltan)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2165(para) 
msgid "This can save an entire round-trip to the client, allowing result counts and pagination to be calculated without an additional <command>COUNT</command> query."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2175(title) 
msgid "Unicode Strings"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2180(para) 
msgid "Support Unicode surrogate pairs (dual 16-bit representation) in <link linkend=\"sql-syntax-strings-uescape\"><literal>U&amp;</literal></link> strings and identifiers (Peter Eisentraut)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2189(para) 
msgid "Support Unicode escapes in <link linkend=\"sql-syntax-strings-escape\"><literal>E'...'</literal></link> strings (Marko Kreen)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2203(title) 
msgid "Object Manipulation"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2208(para) 
msgid "Speed up <link linkend=\"sql-createdatabase\"><command>CREATE DATABASE</command></link> by deferring flushes to disk (Andres Freund, Greg Stark)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2216(para) 
msgid "Allow <link linkend=\"sql-comment\">comments</link> on columns of tables, views, and composite types only, not other relation types such as indexes and <acronym>TOAST</acronym> tables (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2224(para) 
msgid "Allow the creation of <link linkend=\"sql-createtype-enum\">enumerated types</link> containing no values (Bruce Momjian)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2232(para) 
msgid "Let values of columns having storage type <literal>MAIN</literal> remain on the main heap page unless the row cannot fit on a page (Kevin Grittner)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2237(para) 
msgid "Previously <literal>MAIN</literal> values were forced out to <acronym>TOAST</acronym> tables until the row size was less than one-quarter of the page size."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2246(command) 
msgid "ALTER TABLE"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2251(para) 
msgid "Implement <literal>IF EXISTS</literal> for <literal>ALTER TABLE DROP COLUMN</literal> and <literal>ALTER TABLE DROP CONSTRAINT </literal> (Andres Freund)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2258(para) 
msgid "Allow <command>ALTER TABLE</command> commands that rewrite tables to skip <acronym>WAL</acronym> logging (Itagaki Takahiro)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2263(para) 
msgid "Such operations either produce a new copy of the table or are rolled back, so <acronym>WAL</acronym> archiving can be skipped, unless running in continuous archiving mode. This reduces I/O overhead and improves performance."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2272(para) 
msgid "Fix failure of <literal>ALTER TABLE <replaceable>table</replaceable> ADD COLUMN <replaceable>col</replaceable> serial</literal> when done by non-owner of table (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2284(command) 
msgid "CREATE TABLE"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2289(para) 
msgid "Add support for copying <literal>COMMENTS</literal> and <literal>STORAGE</literal> settings in <command>CREATE TABLE ... LIKE</command> commands (Itagaki Takahiro)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2297(para) 
msgid "Add a shortcut for copying all properties in <command>CREATE TABLE ... LIKE</command> commands (Itagaki Takahiro)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2304(para) 
msgid "Add the SQL-standard <literal>CREATE TABLE ... OF <replaceable>type</replaceable></literal> command (Peter Eisentraut)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2310(para) 
msgid "This allows creation of a table that matches an existing composite type. Additional constraints and defaults can be specified in the command."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2322(title) 
msgid "Constraints"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2327(para) 
msgid "Add <link linkend=\"sql-createtable-compatibility\">deferrable unique constraints</link> (Dean Rasheed)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2332(para) 
msgid "This allows mass updates, such as <literal>UPDATE tab SET col = col + 1</literal>, to work reliably on columns that have unique indexes or are marked as primary keys. If the constraint is specified as <literal>DEFERRABLE</literal> it will be checked at the end of the statement, rather than after each row is updated. The constraint check can also be deferred until the end of the current transaction, allowing such updates to be spread over multiple SQL commands."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2346(para) 
msgid "Add <link linkend=\"ddl-constraints-exclusion\">exclusion constraints</link> (Jeff Davis)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2352(para) 
msgid "Exclusion constraints generalize uniqueness constraints by allowing arbitrary comparison operators, not just equality. They are created with the <link linkend=\"sql-createtable-exclude\"><command>CREATE TABLE CONSTRAINT ... EXCLUDE</command></link> clause. The most common use of exclusion constraints is to specify that column entries must not overlap, rather than simply not be equal. This is useful for time periods and other ranges, as well as arrays. This feature enhances checking of data integrity for many calendaring, time-management, and scientific applications."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2366(para) 
msgid "Improve uniqueness-constraint violation error messages to report the values causing the failure (Itagaki Takahiro)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2371(para) 
msgid "For example, a uniqueness constraint violation might now report <literal>Key (x)=(2) already exists</literal>."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2382(title) 
msgid "Object Permissions"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2387(para) 
msgid "Add the ability to make mass permission changes across a whole schema using the new <link linkend=\"sql-grant\"><command>GRANT</command>/<command>REVOKE IN SCHEMA</command></link> clause (Petr Jelinek)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2394(para) 
msgid "This simplifies management of object permissions and makes it easier to utilize database roles for application data security."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2402(para) 
msgid "Add <link linkend=\"sql-alterdefaultprivileges\"><command>ALTER DEFAULT PRIVILEGES</command></link> command to control privileges of objects created later (Petr Jelinek)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2408(para) 
msgid "This greatly simplifies the assignment of object privileges in a complex database application. Default privileges can be set for tables, views, sequences, and functions. Defaults may be assigned on a per-schema basis, or database-wide."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2417(para) 
msgid "Add the ability to control large object (BLOB) permissions with <command>GRANT</command>/<command>REVOKE</command> (KaiGai Kohei)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2422(para) 
msgid "Formerly, any database user could read or modify any large object. Read and write permissions can now be granted and revoked per large object, and the ownership of large objects is tracked."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2436(title) 
msgid "Utility Operations"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2441(para) 
msgid "Make <link linkend=\"sql-listen\"><command>LISTEN</command></link>/<link linkend=\"sql-notify\"><command>NOTIFY</command></link> store pending events in a memory queue, rather than in a system table (Joachim Wieland)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2448(para) 
msgid "This substantially improves performance, while retaining the existing features of transactional support and guaranteed delivery."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2455(para) 
msgid "Allow <link linkend=\"sql-notify\"><command>NOTIFY</command></link> to pass an optional <quote>payload</quote> string to listeners (Joachim Wieland)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2461(para) 
msgid "This greatly improves the usefulness of <command>LISTEN</command>/<command>NOTIFY</command> as a general-purpose event queue system."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2469(para) 
msgid "Allow <link linkend=\"sql-cluster\"><command>CLUSTER</command></link> on all per-database system catalogs (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2474(para) 
msgid "Shared catalogs still cannot be clustered."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2482(command) 
msgid "COPY"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2487(para) 
msgid "Accept <literal>COPY ... CSV FORCE QUOTE *</literal> (Itagaki Takahiro)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2492(para) 
msgid "Now <literal>*</literal> can be used as shorthand for <quote>all columns</quote> in the <literal>FORCE QUOTE</literal> clause."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2499(para) 
msgid "Add new <command>COPY</command> syntax that allows options to be specified inside parentheses (Robert Haas, Emmanuel Cecchet)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2504(para) 
msgid "This allows greater flexibility for future <command>COPY</command> options. The old syntax is still supported, but only for pre-existing options."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2515(command) 
msgid "EXPLAIN"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2520(para) 
msgid "Allow <command>EXPLAIN</command> to output in <acronym>XML</acronym>, <acronym>JSON</acronym>, or <acronym>YAML</acronym> format (Robert Haas, Greg Sabino Mullane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2526(para) 
msgid "The new output formats are easily machine-readable, supporting the development of new tools for analysis of <command>EXPLAIN</command> output."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2533(para) 
msgid "Add new <literal>BUFFERS</literal> option to report query buffer usage during <command>EXPLAIN ANALYZE</command> (Itagaki Takahiro)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2538(para) 
msgid "This allows better query profiling for individual queries. Buffer usage is no longer reported in the output for <link linkend=\"runtime-config-statistics-monitor\">log_statement_stats</link> and related settings."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2547(para) 
msgid "Add hash usage information to <command>EXPLAIN</command> output (Robert Haas)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2554(para) 
msgid "Add new <command>EXPLAIN</command> syntax that allows options to be specified inside parentheses (Robert Haas)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2559(para) 
msgid "This allows greater flexibility for future <command>EXPLAIN</command> options. The old syntax is still supported, but only for pre-existing options."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2570(command) 
msgid "VACUUM"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2575(para) 
msgid "Change <command>VACUUM FULL</command> to rewrite the entire table and rebuild its indexes, rather than moving individual rows around to compact space (Itagaki Takahiro, Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2581(para) 
msgid "The previous method was usually slower and caused index bloat. Note that the new method will use more disk space transiently during <command>VACUUM FULL</command>; potentially as much as twice the space normally occupied by the table and its indexes."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2591(para) 
msgid "Add new <command>VACUUM</command> syntax that allows options to be specified inside parentheses (Itagaki Takahiro)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2596(para) 
msgid "This allows greater flexibility for future <command>VACUUM</command> options. The old syntax is still supported, but only for pre-existing options."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2607(title) 
msgid "Indexes"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2612(para) 
msgid "Allow an index to be named automatically by omitting the index name in <link linkend=\"sql-createindex\"><command>CREATE INDEX</command></link> (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2620(para) 
msgid "By default, multicolumn indexes are now named after all their columns; and index expression columns are now named based on their expressions (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2628(para) 
msgid "Reindexing shared system catalogs is now fully transactional and crash-safe (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2633(para) 
msgid "Formerly, reindexing a shared index was only allowed in standalone mode, and a crash during the operation could leave the index in worse condition than it was before."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2641(para) 
msgid "Add <literal>point_ops</literal> operator class for <acronym>GiST</acronym> (Teodor Sigaev)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2646(para) 
msgid "This feature permits <acronym>GiST</acronym> indexing of <type>point</type> columns. The index can be used for several types of queries such as <replaceable>point</replaceable><literal>&lt;@</literal><replaceable>polygon</replaceable> (point is in polygon). This should make many <productname>PostGIS</productname> queries faster."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2656(para) 
msgid "Use red-black binary trees for <acronym>GIN</acronym> index creation (Teodor Sigaev)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2661(para) 
msgid "Red-black trees are self-balancing. This avoids slowdowns in cases where the input is in nonrandom order."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2680(para) 
msgid "Allow <link linkend=\"datatype-binary\"><type>bytea</type></link> values to be written in hex notation (Peter Eisentraut)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2685(para) 
msgid "The server parameter <link linkend=\"guc-bytea-output\"><varname>bytea_output</varname></link> controls whether hex or traditional format is used for <type>bytea</type> output. Libpq's <function>PQescapeByteaConn()</function> function automatically uses the hex format when connected to <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> 9.0 or newer servers. However, pre-9.0 libpq versions will not correctly process hex format from newer servers."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2695(para) 
msgid "The new hex format will be directly compatible with more applications that use binary data, allowing them to store and retrieve it without extra conversion. It is also significantly faster to read and write than the traditional format."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2704(para) 
msgid "Allow server parameter <link linkend=\"guc-extra-float-digits\">extra_float_digits</link> to be increased to <literal>3</literal> (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2710(para) 
msgid "The previous maximum <varname>extra_float_digits</varname> setting was <literal>2</literal>. There are cases where 3 digits are needed to dump and restore <type>float4</type> values exactly. <application>pg_dump</application> will now use the setting of 3 when dumping from a server that allows it."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2719(para) 
msgid "Tighten input checking for <type>int2vector</type> values (Caleb Welton)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2728(link) 
msgid "Full Text Search"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2733(para) 
msgid "Add prefix support in <literal>synonym</literal> dictionaries (Teodor Sigaev)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2740(para) 
msgid "Add <firstterm>filtering</firstterm> dictionaries (Teodor Sigaev)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2744(para) 
msgid "Filtering dictionaries allow tokens to be modified then passed to subsequent dictionaries."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2751(para) 
msgid "Allow underscores in email-address tokens (Teodor Sigaev)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2757(para) 
msgid "Use more standards-compliant rules for parsing <acronym>URL</acronym> tokens (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2770(title) 
msgid "Functions"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2775(para) 
msgid "Allow function calls to supply parameter names and match them to named parameters in the function definition (Pavel Stehule)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2780(para) 
msgid "For example, if a function is defined to take parameters <literal>a</literal> and <literal>b</literal>, it can be called with <literal>func(a := 7, b := 12)</literal> or <literal>func(b := 12, a := 7)</literal>."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2788(para) 
msgid "Support locale-specific <link linkend=\"functions-posix-regexp\">regular expression</link> processing with <acronym>UTF-8</acronym> server encoding (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2794(para) 
msgid "Locale-specific regular expression functionality includes case-insensitive matching and locale-specific character classes. Previously, these features worked correctly for non-<acronym>ASCII</acronym> characters only if the database used a single-byte server encoding (such as LATIN1). They will still misbehave in multi-byte encodings other than <acronym>UTF-8</acronym>."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2805(para) 
msgid "Add support for scientific notation in <link linkend=\"functions-formatting\"><function>to_char()</function></link> (<link linkend=\"functions-formatting-numeric-table\"><literal>EEEE</literal> specification</link>) (Pavel Stehule, Brendan Jurd)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2815(para) 
msgid "Make <function>to_char()</function> honor <link linkend=\"functions-formatting-datetimemod-table\"><literal>FM</literal></link> (fill mode) in <literal>Y</literal>, <literal>YY</literal>, and <literal>YYY</literal> specifications (Bruce Momjian, Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2822(para) 
msgid "It was already honored by <literal>YYYY</literal>."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2828(para) 
msgid "Fix <function>to_char()</function> to output localized numeric and monetary strings in the correct encoding on <productname>Windows</productname> (Hiroshi Inoue, Itagaki Takahiro, Bruce Momjian)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2836(para) 
msgid "Correct calculations of <link linkend=\"functions-geometry-op-table\"><quote>overlaps</quote></link> and <quote>contains</quote> operations for polygons (Teodor Sigaev)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2842(para) 
msgid "The polygon <literal>&amp;&amp;</literal> (overlaps) operator formerly just checked to see if the two polygons' bounding boxes overlapped. It now does a more correct check. The polygon <literal>@&gt;</literal> and <literal>&lt;@</literal> (contains/contained by) operators formerly checked to see if one polygon's vertexes were all contained in the other; this can wrongly report <quote>true</quote> for some non-convex polygons. Now they check that all line segments of one polygon are contained in the other."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2857(title) 
msgid "Aggregates"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2862(para) 
msgid "Allow aggregate functions to use <link linkend=\"syntax-aggregates\"><literal>ORDER BY</literal></link> (Andrew Gierth)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2867(para) 
msgid "For example, this is now supported: <literal>array_agg(a ORDER BY b)</literal>. This is useful with aggregates for which the order of input values is significant, and eliminates the need to use a nonstandard subquery to determine the ordering."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2876(para) 
msgid "Multi-argument aggregate functions can now use <literal>DISTINCT</literal> (Andrew Gierth)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2883(para) 
msgid "Add the <link linkend=\"functions-aggregate-table\"><function>string_agg()</function></link> aggregate function to combine values into a single string (Pavel Stehule)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2892(para) 
msgid "Aggregate functions that are called with <literal>DISTINCT</literal> are now passed NULL values if the aggregate transition function is not marked as <literal>STRICT</literal> (Andrew Gierth)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2898(para) 
msgid "For example, <literal>agg(DISTINCT x)</literal> might pass a NULL <literal>x</literal> value to <function>agg()</function>. This is more consistent with the behavior in non-<literal>DISTINCT</literal> cases."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2910(title) 
msgid "Bit Strings"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2915(para) 
msgid "Add <link linkend=\"functions-binarystring-other\"><function>get_bit()</function></link> and <function>set_bit()</function> functions for <type>bit</type> strings, mirroring those for <type>bytea</type> (Leonardo F)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2925(para) 
msgid "Implement <link linkend=\"functions-string-sql\"><function>OVERLAY()</function></link> (replace) for <type>bit</type> strings and <type>bytea</type> (Leonardo F)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2938(title) 
msgid "Object Information Functions"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2943(para) 
msgid "Add <link linkend=\"functions-admin-dbsize\"><function>pg_table_size()</function></link> and <function>pg_indexes_size()</function> to provide a more user-friendly interface to the <function>pg_relation_size()</function> function (Bernd Helmle)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2953(para) 
msgid "Add <link linkend=\"functions-info-access-table\"><function>has_sequence_privilege()</function></link> for sequence permission checking (Abhijit Menon-Sen)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2961(para) 
msgid "Update the <link linkend=\"information-schema\">information_schema</link> views to conform to SQL:2008 (Peter Eisentraut)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2969(para) 
msgid "Make the <literal>information_schema</literal> views correctly display maximum octet lengths for <type>char</type> and <type>varchar</type> columns (Peter Eisentraut)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2977(para) 
msgid "Speed up <literal>information_schema</literal> privilege views (Joachim Wieland)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2988(title) 
msgid "Function and Trigger Creation"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2993(para) 
msgid "Support execution of anonymous code blocks using the <link linkend=\"sql-do\"><command>DO</command></link> statement (Petr Jelinek, Joshua Tolley, Hannu Valtonen)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:2999(para) 
msgid "This allows execution of server-side code without the need to create and delete a temporary function definition. Code can be executed in any language for which the user has permissions to define a function."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3007(para) 
msgid "Implement SQL-standard-compliant <link linkend=\"sql-createtrigger\">per-column triggers</link> (Itagaki Takahiro)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3013(para) 
msgid "Such triggers are fired only when the specified column(s) are affected by the query, e.g. appear in an <command>UPDATE</command>'s <literal>SET</literal> list."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3021(para) 
msgid "Add the <literal>WHEN</literal> clause to <link linkend=\"sql-createtrigger\"><command>CREATE TRIGGER</command></link> to allow control over whether a trigger is fired (Itagaki Takahiro)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3028(para) 
msgid "While the same type of check can always be performed inside the trigger, doing it in an external <literal>WHEN</literal> clause can have performance benefits."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3042(title) 
msgid "Server-Side Languages"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3047(para) 
msgid "Add the <literal>OR REPLACE</literal> clause to <link linkend=\"sql-createlanguage\"><command>CREATE LANGUAGE</command></link> (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3053(para) 
msgid "This is helpful to optionally install a language if it does not already exist, and is particularly helpful now that PL/pgSQL is installed by default."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3063(title) 
msgid "<link linkend=\"plpgsql\">PL/pgSQL</link> Server-Side Language"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3069(para) 
msgid "Install PL/pgSQL by default (Bruce Momjian)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3073(para) 
msgid "The language can still be removed from a particular database if the administrator has security or performance concerns about making it available."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3081(para) 
msgid "Improve handling of cases where PL/pgSQL variable names conflict with identifiers used in queries within a function (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3087(para) 
msgid "The default behavior is now to throw an error when there is a conflict, so as to avoid surprising behaviors. This can be modified, via the configuration parameter <link linkend=\"plpgsql-var-subst\"><varname>plpgsql.variable_conflict</varname></link> or the per-function option <literal>#variable_conflict</literal>, to allow either the variable or the query-supplied column to be used. In any case PL/pgSQL will no longer attempt to substitute variables in places where they would not be syntactically valid."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3100(para) 
msgid "Make PL/pgSQL use the main lexer, rather than its own version (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3105(para) 
msgid "This ensures accurate tracking of the main system's behavior for details such as string escaping. Some user-visible details, such as the set of keywords considered reserved in PL/pgSQL, have changed in consequence."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3114(para) 
msgid "Avoid throwing an unnecessary error for an invalid record reference (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3123(programlisting) 
#, no-wrap
msgid "\nif TG_OP = 'INSERT' and NEW.col1 = ... then\n"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3119(para) 
msgid "An error is now thrown only if the reference is actually fetched, rather than whenever the enclosing expression is reached. For example, many people have tried to do this in triggers: <placeholder-1/> This will now actually work as expected."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3131(para) 
msgid "Improve PL/pgSQL's ability to handle row types with dropped columns (Pavel Stehule)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3138(para) 
msgid "Allow input parameters to be assigned values within PL/pgSQL functions (Steve Prentice)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3143(para) 
msgid "Formerly, input parameters were treated as being declared <literal>CONST</literal>, so the function's code could not change their values. This restriction has been removed to simplify porting of functions from other DBMSes that do not impose the equivalent restriction. An input parameter now acts like a local variable initialized to the passed-in value."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3154(para) 
msgid "Improve error location reporting in PL/pgSQL (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3160(para) 
msgid "Add <replaceable>count</replaceable> and <literal>ALL</literal> options to <command>MOVE FORWARD</command>/<literal>BACKWARD</literal> in PL/pgSQL (Pavel Stehule)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3167(para) 
msgid "Allow PL/pgSQL's <literal>WHERE CURRENT OF</literal> to use a cursor variable (Tom Lane)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3174(para) 
msgid "Allow PL/pgSQL's <command>OPEN <replaceable>cursor</replaceable> FOR EXECUTE</command> to use parameters (Pavel Stehule, Itagaki Takahiro)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3179(para) 
msgid "This is accomplished with a new <literal>USING</literal> clause."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3189(title) 
msgid "<link linkend=\"plperl\">PL/Perl</link> Server-Side Language"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3194(para) 
msgid "Add new PL/Perl functions: <link linkend=\"plperl-utility-functions\"><function>quote_literal()</function></link>, <function>quote_nullable()</function>, <function>quote_ident()</function>, <function>encode_bytea()</function>, <function>decode_bytea()</function>, <function>looks_like_number()</function>, <function>encode_array_literal()</function>, <function>encode_array_constructor()</function> (Tim Bunce)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3206(para) 
msgid "Add server parameter <link linkend=\"guc-plperl-on-init\"><varname>plperl.on_init</varname></link> to specify a PL/Perl initialization function (Tim Bunce)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3213(para) 
msgid "<link linkend=\"guc-plperl-on-plperl-init\"><varname>plperl.on_plperl_init</varname></link> and <link linkend=\"guc-plperl-on-plperl-init\"><varname>plperl.on_plperlu_init</varname></link> are also available for initialization that is specific to the trusted or untrusted language respectively."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3224(para) 
msgid "Support <command>END</command> blocks in PL/Perl (Tim Bunce)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3228(para) 
msgid "<command>END</command> blocks do not currently allow database access."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3234(para) 
msgid "Allow <command>use strict</command> in PL/Perl (Tim Bunce)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3238(para) 
msgid "Perl <literal>strict</literal> checks can also be globally enabled with the new server parameter <link linkend=\"guc-plperl-use-strict\"><varname>plperl.use_strict</varname></link>."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3246(para) 
msgid "Allow <command>require</command> in PL/Perl (Tim Bunce)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3250(para) 
msgid "This basically tests to see if the module is loaded, and if not, generates an error. It will not allow loading of modules that the administrator has not preloaded via the initialization parameters."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3258(para) 
msgid "Allow <command>use feature</command> in PL/Perl if Perl version 5.10 or later is used (Tim Bunce)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3265(para) 
msgid "Verify that PL/Perl return values are valid in the server encoding (Andrew Dunstan)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3276(title) 
msgid "<link linkend=\"plpython\">PL/Python</link> Server-Side Language"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3281(para) 
msgid "Add Unicode support in PL/Python (Peter Eisentraut)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3285(para) 
msgid "Strings are automatically converted from/to the server encoding as necessary."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3292(para) 
msgid "Improve <type>bytea</type> support in PL/Python (Caleb Welton)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3296(para) 
msgid "<type>Bytea</type> values passed into PL/Python are now represented as binary, rather than the PostgreSQL <type>bytea</type> text format. <type>Bytea</type> values containing null bytes are now also output properly from PL/Python. Passing of boolean, integer, and float values was also improved."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3306(para) 
msgid "Support <link linkend=\"plpython-arrays\">arrays</link> as parameters and return values in PL/Python (Peter Eisentraut)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3313(para) 
msgid "Improve mapping of SQL domains to Python types (Peter Eisentraut)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3319(para) 
msgid "Add <application>Python</application> 3 support to PL/Python (Peter Eisentraut)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3323(para) 
msgid "The new server-side language is called <link linkend=\"plpython-python23\"><literal>plpython3u</literal></link>. This cannot be used in the same session with the <application>Python</application> 2 server-side language."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3332(para) 
msgid "Improve error location and exception reporting in PL/Python (Peter Eisentraut)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3344(title) 
msgid "Client Applications"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3349(para) 
msgid "Add an <option>--analyze-only</option> option to <link linkend=\"app-vacuumdb\"><command>vacuumdb</command></link>, to analyze without vacuuming (Bruce Momjian)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3359(application) 
msgid "psql"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-Bcej/release-9.0.xml:3364(para) 
msgid "Add support for quoting/escaping the values of <application>psql</application><link linkend=\"app-psql-variables\">variables</link> as SQL strings or identifiers (Pavel Stehule, Robert Haas)"
